-- CANADA STOCKS-TSX opens higher as energy shares gain with oil price
-- By John Tilak
-- Thu May 29, 2014 09:36AM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, May 29 (Reuters) - Canada's main stock index opened higher on Thursday as stronger oil prices helped drive up shares of energy producers, offsetting a decline in Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce <CM.TO> after the lender reported quarterly results.

